Title: Object: Habit of a Bashaw of Egypt in 1749 / Bacha d'Egipte
Series: A Collection of the Dresses of Different Nations
Series: Recueil des habillements de différentes nations
Description: Plate 85: a man, whole-length standing slightly to the left, looking towards the viewer, wearing turban and robe, his right hand at his waist, his left hand at the hilt of his sword which is shaped as an animal. Etching
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of 480 numbered costume plates, arranged in four volumes, for comment see 1895,1031.240.
